deck: A corrupt cop and partner of Mac
description:
Origin

After witnessing a bank robbery that went wrong when he was a child, the deeply amoral Roy decided that the easiest way to earn money and respect was to become a corrupt cop. To this end he joined the LAPD, where he eventually became an extremely corrupt detective along with his partner, Mac.

Creation

Roy was created by Nick Spencer and Steve Lieber. He made his first appearance in The Fix #1.

Major Story Arcs

The Fix

Together with Mac, Roy carries out a series of crimes in an effort to pay back a debt to their boss, Josh. When they gamble their money away without giving any to Josh, he offers to forgive the debt if they can smuggle something through LAX. Roy shoots Mac in the hand in order to get him assigned to working with the K-9 unit. While Mac is in hospital, Roy fakes a suicide attempt in order to lure fellow officer Pete Danielson into helping him with a case so that he can frame Pete for murder and take over a security detail Pete was assigned. Following a tumultuous security shift with a young starlet, he witnesses the murder of his charge and narrowly escapes the explosion of her house.

Powers and Abilities

Roy is a competent, if not particularly conscientious, detective. He has received the basic weapons and procedural training given to police officers. He is conniving and ruthless in coming up with criminal plans to benefit himself.
name: Roy Garney

deck: A corrupt cop and partner of Roy
description:
Origin

Very little is known about Mac. At some point he became a police officer with the LAPD, and was partnered with Roy. Either under Roy's influence, or sometime before they were partnered, he became corrupt.

Creation

Mac was created by Nick Spencer and Steve Lieber. He made his first appearance in The Fix #1.

Major Story Arcs

The Fix

Together with Roy, Mac carries out a series of crimes in an effort to pay back a debt to their boss, Josh. When they gamble their money away without giving any to Josh, he offers to forgive the debt if they can smuggle something through LAX. Mac reluctantly allows Roy to shoot him in the hand so that he will be assigned to the K-9 unit. After spending some time in the hospital, he is partnered with Pretzels, who takes an instant dislike to Mac. After they take down a drug smuggler together, Mac and Pretzels finally bond, allowing Josh's smuggling plot to move forward.

Powers and Abilities

Mac is a competent detective, and has received the basic weapons and procedural training given to police officers.
